Former Njuri Ncheke Council of Elders chairman Paul M'Ethingia has died after a short illness.
According to the family, the 81-year-old elder died on Saturday after developing blood sugar complications the previous day.
"He was rushed to hospital but passed on on Jamhuri Day while the condition was being managed. He has been healthy and going on with his business. Burial arrangements are ongoing," his son Isaac Mutuma said.



