Several leaders eulogised Mr M'Ethingia as a wise elder who pursued peace and helped secure the future of Njuri Ncheke by allowing professionals to be initiated into the group.
National Council of Elders Chairman Phares Rutere, who is a former Njuri Ncheke secretary-general, said Mr M'Ethingia took over as chairman in 1987.
M'Ethingia was the fifth chairman after paramount chief M'Angaine M'Ithiiria, chief M'Ikiugu Gathinya, senior chief M'Anampiu Kaigwara and paramount chief Naaman Mwirichia.



