Very articulate
"We have lost an elder who was very articulate on Njuri Ncheke affairs. He taught many of us the rich ideologies of Njuri Ncheke and was committed to the welfare of the Ameru. He was behind the inclusion of professionals in the council which has enabled continuity of Njuri Ncheke in a fast-evolving world," Mr Rutere said.
Njuri Ncheke Operations Secretary-General Mbaya Muthamia said Mr M'Ethingia was an articulate elder who fought against female genital mutilation and helped in the resolution of many land disputes.
Mr Josrphat Murangiri, the secretary-general in charge of programmes, said they intend to give M'Ethingia a state burial for his role in promoting the Ameru culture.
M'Ethingia was among a group of elders who backed former Libyan president Muammar Gaddafi's dream of a United States of Africa.



